of   Lyall  ."]}]},{"name":"Bouchard","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Marcel, Andre, Michel, Normand, Pierre, Cecile, Gilles, Lucien, Alphonse, Jacques, Alain.","French: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Burchard</i>, composed of the elements <i>burg</i> ‘protection’ and <i>hard</i> ‘hard, strong’.","French: in some cases, possibly also a nickname for someone with a big mouth (in either a literal or figurative sense), from <i>bouche</i> ‘mouth’ + the pejorative suffix <i>-ard</i>. Compare   Buschor  ,   Bushard  ,   Bushaw  , and   Bushor  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Bushard","meanings":["Americanized form of French   Bouchard  .","Possibly, in some cases, also an Americanized form of German <b>Buschard</b> (see   Bushart   2)."]},{"name":"Buschor","meanings":["Swiss German: probably a Germanized form of French   Bouchard  . Compare   Buschur   and   Bushor  ."]},{"name":"Bushore","meanings":["Americanized form of French   Bouchard  , reflecting the characteristic Canadian and American French rounding of the <i>-ard</i> ending. Compare   Bushor  ."]}]},{"name":"Bartholomew","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of New Testament origin, the name of an apostle mentioned in all the synoptic gospels (Matthew, Mark, and Luke) and in the Acts of the Apostles. It is an Aramaic formation meaning ‘son of Talmai’, and has been assumed by many scholars to be a byname of the apostle   Nathaniel .  <i>Talmai</i> is a Hebrew name, said to mean ‘abounding in furrows’ (Numbers 13:22)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Bartholomew de L'isle Bouchard was born in 1049, in L'Île Bouchard, Indre-et-Loire, Centre, France, his father, Archimbaud Borel, was 30 and his mother, Amabilis Isle Bouchard, was 26. He had at least 1 daughter with Gerberge de Blaison. He died in 1097, i